# Implementation Plan - Patients Feature Clean Architecture & Rules Refactoring

This plan aligns the `patients` feature with the project's architecture guidelines and rules by removing direct `MockData` imports from `PatientsCubit`, routing all data flow through a repository using the `ICloudService` interface, and enabling dependency injection for the Cubit.

## Proposed Changes

### Core Services

#### [MODIFY] [mock_cloud_service.dart](file:///c:/flutter Projects/clinics system/Clinic Pro/clinic_pro/lib/core/services/mock_cloud_service.dart)
- Support selecting from `patient_visits` and `patient_prescription_records` mock tables to map database-independent queries.

### Patients Feature - Data & Domain Layers

#### [NEW] [patients_repository.dart](file:///c:/flutter Projects/clinics system/Clinic Pro/clinic_pro/lib/features/patients/presentation/manager/patients_repository.dart)
- Implement `PatientsRepository` class using the `ICloudService` dependency.
- Define methods:
  - `loadPatients()`: Calls `_cloud.select(table: 'patients')`.
  - `addPatient(...)`: Calls `_cloud.insert(table: 'patients', data: ...)`.
  - `updatePatient(...)`: Calls `_cloud.update(table: 'patients', data: ..., matchColumn: 'id', matchValue: ...)`.
  - `getVisitsForPatient(...)`: Calls `_cloud.select(table: 'patient_visits', eq: {'patient_id': ...})`.
  - `getPrescriptionsForPatient(...)`: Calls `_cloud.select(table: 'patient_prescription_records', eq: {'patient_id': ...})`.
  - `findPatientById(...)`: Calls `_cloud.select(table: 'patients', eq: {'id': ...})`.

